f2c79d4fc1f1f0fea221b54ea0d4c03a1a928fdb.commit.message:
[WSS-194] - Support overriding KeyStore alias for signature so that it can be different than user name used for UsernameToken
 - I added WSHandlerConstants.SIGNATURE_USER to specify a different "signature user" from WSHandlerConstants.USER
 - This is consistent with the previous pattern of ENCRYPTION_USER
 - A side-effect is that the SignatureAction now relies on RequestData.getSignatureUser() rather than getUser
 - Added a test for this issue as well.

855330da01ff32268306a5b6fbe3610286db90b0.commit.message:
[WSS-191] - Moved trust verification from WSHandler to SignatureProcessor
 - Trust is now verified on certificates *before* signature validation
 - This means that bad requests are rejected quicker
 - Also it works around a security bug in the WSHandler implementations where trust is only verified on a single certificate
 - Also did a general rewrite of the SignatureProcessor
855330da01ff32268306a5b6fbe3610286db90b0.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh
